e OS processes started |\n| 2018-09-04 14:18:27 | User session begins (`userinit.exe` \u2192 `explorer.exe` PID 4508) |\n| 2018-09-05 14:27:55 | `ftusbsrvc.exe` (PID 4916) starts, opens listener on TCP 33001 |\n| 2018-09-06 17:08:20 | `usbclient.exe` (PID 6648) launched from `explorer.exe` \u2014 likely user-delivered dropper |\n| 2018-09-06 17:13:49 | Network activity spike (multiple svchost UDP sockets open) |\n| 2018-09-06 17:17:20 | `license_ctrl.e` (PID 1716) starts, opens TCP listener on 5682 (IPv4+IPv6) |\n| 2018-09-06 (ongoing) | Repeated CLOSED TCP connections to 172.16.4.10:8080 \u2014 C2 beaconing |\n\n## Indicators of Compromise\n\n| IOC | Type | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `license_ctrl.e` | Process | Backdoor listener \u2014 non-existent Windows process |\n| `usbclient.exe` | Process | Dropper/implant launched from explorer.exe |\n| `ftusbsrvc.exe` | Process | Suspicious service listener on TCP 33001 |\n| `172.16.4.10` | IP Address | C2 server \u2014 repeated connections on port 8080 |\n| TCP 5682 | Port | Backdoor listener port (license_ctrl.e) |\n| TCP 33001 | Port | Backdoor listener port (ftusbsrvc.exe) |\n| TCP 8080 \u2192 172.16.4.10 | Network | C2 beaconing channel |\n\n## Persistence Mechanisms\n\nRegistry Run key and service-based persistence could not be confirmed via regripper due to tool limitations (hive extraction required). However, `ftusbsrvc.exe`'s naming convention (ending in `srvc`) strongly suggests service-based persistence (T1543.003). `license_ctrl.e`'s all-interface listener suggests it is configured to survive reboots. Full persistence confirmation requires registry hive extraction from the disk image.\n\n## Recommendations\n\n1. **Isolate 172.16.5.25 immediately** \u2014 block all traffic to/from 172.16.4.10.\n2. **Block at perimeter**: 172.16.4.10, TCP/8080 outbound, TCP/5682 inbound, TCP/33001 inbound.\n3. **Hunt laterally** \u2014 check all hosts for `usbclient.exe`, `license_ctrl.e`, `ftusbsrvc.exe`.\n4. **Extract disk